release_note: Now the official App of Harmony: A New Musical on Broadway!
Please feel free to reach out regarding any issues using the email link in the app. In this version I changed the placement of Ads and fixed an image error with older versions of iOS.
Fixed issue to show text with blow mode and settings instructions that weren t showing up on some phones.
New design to improve ease of use. Fixed issues with newer screen sizes. Fixed a few other small bugs.
New labels for the piano notes. Updated review link.
Fixed a small bug with the piano buttons and added an awesome loading screen instead of just having a blank one!
Fixed a bug with the No Ads In App Purchase!
Allows the option to remove the Ad Banner for 0.99.
Ad fixed which keeps the app free! :
For advice from professional singers and coaches a link to the Singer Stories podcast has been added. Upgraded pitch pipe audio Upgraded piano audio Some graphics changed

A new menu for the pitch pipe adding grid layout f octave toggle mode and blow mode! Grid layout is mainly to help users with smaller phones who may prefer larger buttons. The F octave pitch pipe was added because two is better than one! Toggle mode was added just incase users don t like holding down the button. Blow mode was added because why the heck not. Now you can blow into your phone to play a pitch just like a real pitch pipe!

The audio files of the Pitch Pipe function have been updated. The original audio files are of a person blowing into an actual pitch pipe. This was used for people who would prefer that authentic sound instead of an electronic tone. It was discovered that some of the audio had some tuning variations at times of 10 Hz . This was most likely due to imperfections in the physical Pitch Pipe used in the recordings. This isn t a huge variation to the ears of a casual user but it was worth improving upon. The audio s pitches have been adjusted to now be within 2 Hz but most often it is less. Note: this is using 440Hz tuning If you find further problems with this audio please feel free to email me directly at johnpocketpitch yahoo.com. I would prefer to fix problems rather than have people dismiss the App. Thank you John Walbolt
Keyboard is now 6 octaves C1 C7 to cover the vocal ranges of Bass to Soprano. Keyboard can now play multiple notes at the same time! Keyboard notes play after touch and do not need to be held down.
Added a Keyboard for greater range of pitches Added an open letter to the users for feedback and improvement Added a small iAD banner to allow App to remain FREE
